
Provides utility code to use in php projects.
Designed to copy the code needed, and nothing else.
No dependency management

Installation is done by hand :
- in a project using tiglib, create a directory that will contain tiglib code (for example vendor/tiglib)
- in this directory, copy src/autoload.php
- copy one by one the files you need, reproducing the hierarchy.

Example :
vendor/tiglib
    ├── autoload.php
    └── time
        └── HHMM2minutes.php

In your code :
require_once 'vendor/tiglib/autoload.php';
use \tiglib\time\HHMM2minutes;
echo HHMM2minutes::compute('12:34') . "\n";

---------- unit tests ----------
phpunit --bootstrap autoload.php 
phpunit --bootstrap autoload.php time/HHMM2minutesTest.php
